pesticide.PPE: Protective eyewear, a long-sleeved shirt, long pants, shoes, socks, and a NIOSH-approved particulate respirator with any N, R, or P filter with NIOSH approval number prefix TC-84A or a NIOSH-approved powered air-purifying respirator with an HE filter with NIOSH approval number prefix TC-21C.

Safety_Information.general_Info: For non-emergency information concerning this product, call the National Pesticide Information Center (NPIC) at 1-800-858-7378. For emergencies, call your local poison control center at 1-800-222-1222.
Safety_Information.if_In_Eyes: Hold eye open and rinse slowly and gently with water for 15-20 minutes. Remove contact lenses, if present, after the first 5 minutes, then continue rinsing eye. Contact a poison control center or doctor for treatment advice.
Safety_Information.physician_Note: Have the product container or label with you when calling a poison control center or doctor or going for treatment.
